.button {
    width: 100px;
    transition: width 0.3s ease;
}
.button:hover {
    width: 150px;
}
Gradient Backgrounds:
Create gradients to add depth and dimension to backgrounds.

css
Copy code
/* Example: Creating a gradient background for a container */
.container {
    background: linear-gradient(45deg, #3498db, #1abc9c);
}
Keyframe Animations:
Create custom animations using keyframes.

css
Copy code
/* Example: Create a bouncing animation for an element */
@keyframes bounce {
    0%, 20%, 50%, 80%, 100% {
        transform: translateY(0);
    }
    40% {
        transform: translateY(-20px);
    }
    60% {
        transform: translateY(-10px);
    }
}
.animated-element {
    animation: bounce 2s infinite;
}
Transformations:
Apply scale, rotate, or skew transformations to elements.

css
Copy code
/* Example: Rotate an image on hover */
.image:hover {
    transform: rotate(15deg);
}
Filters:
Use CSS filters to adjust the visual appearance of elements.

css
Copy code
/* Example: Apply a grayscale filter to an image */
.grayscale-image {
    filter: grayscale(100%);
}
Text Effects:
Add text effects like gradients and outlines.

css
Copy code
/* Example: Add a gradient text color */
.gradient-text {
    background: linear-gradient(45deg, #3498db, #1abc9c);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    background-clip: text;
    color: transparent;
}
Animations on Scroll:
Use libraries like ScrollMagic or native CSS @scroll-timeline to trigger animations as users scroll down the page.

Remember to adjust these styles according to your website's design and requirements. Additionally, always consider performance and user experience when adding special effects, as excessive animations and transitions can impact page load times and usability.





.container {
    background: linear-gradient(45deg, #3498db, #1abc9c);
}
@keyframes bounce {
    0%, 20%, 50%, 80%, 100% {
        transform: translateY(0);
    }
    40% {
        transform: translateY(-20px);
    }
    60% {
        transform: translateY(-10px);
    }
}
.animated-element {
    animation: bounce 2s infinite;
}
